<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[700,1229,956,1741]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
COMMENTS: This specimen bears the name 
<taxonomicName box="[700,887,1132,1155]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eximia">
<emphasis box="[700,887,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Luscinia eximia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Brehm’s hand, the Rothschild Collection label bears the correct data, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[751,981,1190,1213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="4 - 63" refId="ref96698" refString="Hartert, E. 1918 a. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. A. Types in the Brehm Collection. Novitates Zoologicae 25: 4 - 63." type="journal article" year="1918">Hartert (1918a: 34)</bibRefCitation>
, in designating it the 
<typeStatus box="[700,810,1220,1243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">lectotype</typeStatus>
, correctly gave the data. However, the Rothschild type labels for this specimen and for the type of 
<taxonomicName box="[935,1134,1279,1302]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hybrida">
<emphasis box="[935,1134,1279,1302]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Luscinia hybrida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, below, were reversed, so a corrected AMNH type label has been added. AMNH 454823, adult male from 
<collectingRegion box="[836,944,1366,1389]" country="Hungary" name="Budapest" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Budapest</collectingRegion>
(5 Pesth), collected in 
<date box="[700,826,1396,1419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1838-05">May 1838</date>
, and labeled 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1067,1396,1419]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eximia">
<emphasis box="[990,1067,1396,1419]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">eximia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Brehm is the only 
<typeStatus box="[812,969,1425,1448]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paralectotype</typeStatus>
in AMNH. This had been mistakenly cataloged at AMNH as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">pomarina</emphasis>
. A third specimen, AMNH 454820, incorrectly cataloged as 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1103,1513,1536]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eximia">
<emphasis box="[1026,1103,1513,1536]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">eximia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is from ‘‘Pommern’’, is labeled as 
<emphasis box="[1066,1179,1543,1566]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">pomarina</emphasis>
by Brehm, and is not a 
<typeStatus box="[945,1102,1572,1595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paralectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1144,1221,1572,1595]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="eximia">
<emphasis box="[1144,1221,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">eximia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[700,1229,956,1741]" lastBlockId="11.[123,651,193,275]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<bibRefCitation author="Ripley, S. D." box="[729,941,1601,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="13 - 227" refId="ref102558" refString="Ripley, S. D. 1964. Family Muscicapidae. Subfamily Turdinae. In E. Mayr and R. A. Paynter, Jr. (editors), Check-list of birds of the world, vol. 10: 13 - 227. Cambridge, MA: Museum of Comparative Zoology, 502 pp." type="book chapter" year="1964">Ripley (1964: 40)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="luscinia (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1060,1152,1601,1624]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luscinia">
<emphasis box="[1060,1152,1601,1624]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">luscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1800" box="[779,892,1631,1654]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Erithacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,892,1631,1654]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Erithacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sibley, C. G. &amp; B. L. Monroe, Jr." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref104528" refString="Sibley, C. G., and B. L. Monroe, Jr. 1990. Distribution and taxonomy of birds of the world. New Haven, CT: Yale University Press, 1111 pp." type="book" year="1990">Sibley and Monroe (1990: 532)</bibRefCitation>
treated the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. Forster" authorityYear="1817" box="[983,1083,1660,1683]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[983,1083,1660,1683]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Luscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[700,821,1689,1712]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Saxicolini">Saxicolini</taxonomicName>
, subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[962,1127,1689,1712]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Muscicapinae">Muscicapinae</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref93312" refString="Dickinson, E. C. (editor). 2003. The Howard and Moore complete checklist of the birds of the world. 3 rd ed. London: Christopher Helm, 1039 pp." type="book" year="2003">Dickinson (2003: 675)</bibRefCitation>
placed it in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vigors" authorityYear="1825" box="[123,262,193,216]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Saxicolinae">Saxicolinae</taxonomicName>
, family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1822" box="[357,522,193,216]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Muscicapidae</taxonomicName>
. Molecular studies of 
<taxonomicName authority="luscinia" authorityName="luscinia (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[251,455,223,246]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Luscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luscinia">
<emphasis box="[251,455,223,246]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Luscinia luscinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wink, M. &amp; H. Sauer-Gurth &amp; E. Gwinner" box="[123,349,252,275]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="349 - 355" refId="ref107453" refString="Wink, M., H. Sauer-Gurth, and E. Gwinner. 2002 a. Evolutionary relationships of stonechats and related species inferred from mitochrondrial-DNA sequences and genomic fingerprinting. British Birds 95: 349 - 355." type="journal article" year="2002">Wink et al. (2002a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wink, M. &amp; H. Saur-Gurth &amp; P. Heidrich &amp; H. - H. Witt &amp; E. Gwinner" box="[363,441,252,275]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="22 - 30" refId="ref107493" refString="Wink, M., H. Saur-Gurth, P. Heidrich, H. - H. Witt, and E. Gwinner. 2002 b. A molecular phylogeny of stonechats and related turdids, pp. 22 - 30. In E. Urquhart. Stonechats. A guide to the genus Saxicola. New Haven, CT: Yale University Press, 320 pp." type="book chapter" year="2002">2002b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
